<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[151,296,582,607]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,582,607]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Female. Fore wing 
<quantity box="[530,621,582,606]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="7.2">7.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[634,695,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[713,799,582,606]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–90" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1800,1823]" captionTargetBox="[256,1339,155,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-239@63.[255,1339,155,1783]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 73–90. ♀. 73–84, head, frontal, Holotypes. 73, Debilos soror (Trentepohl). 74, D. dialeucor sp. nov. 75, D. dnopheror sp. nov. 76, D. orthum sp. nov. 77, D. gnampthum sp. nov. 78, D. typurum sp. nov. 79, D. prionilix sp. nov. 80, D. owinum sp. nov. 81, D. pekujum sp. nov. 82, D. crusilix sp. nov. 83, D. frater sp. nov. 84, D. indistinctum sp. nov. 85, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti), head, frontal. Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 86, 87, clypeus, lateral. 86, D. soror (Trentepohl). Specimen from Brazil, PA, Serra Norte, Pedreira, 19–22.VI.1985 (MPEG). 87, D. palaior sp. nov., Holotype. 88, D. dnopheror sp. nov., left antenna, dorsal. Specimen from Brazil, PA, Melgaço, Floresta Nacional de Caxiuanã, 18–21.ix.2003 (UFES). 89, 90, pedicel and flagellomere 1, dorsal, Holotypes. 89, D. orthum sp. nov. 90, D. gnampthum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 73 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
): Antenna with 27–28 flagellomeres. Clypeus punctate, moderately convex, most prominent dorsally, CWH 1.90; MWC 0.69, MLW 1.90, MWW 0.40; malar space moderately long, MSM 1.00; supra-antennal area with almost indistinct, median, longitudinal carina; minimum distance from eye margin to occipital carina laterally approximately same width of mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName box="[199,319,725,748]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,319,725,748]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[343,438,724,748]" captionStart="FIGURES 96–100" captionStartId="65.[151,263,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[198,1388,193,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-70@65.[198,1388,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 96–100. Holotypes, ♀, lateral. 96, Debilos orthum sp. nov. 97, D. gnampthum sp. nov. 98, D. frater sp. nov. 99, D. prionilix sp. nov. 100, D. crusilix sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Pronotum lateral portion next to collar inconspicuously strigate-rugose, next to mesopleuron inconspicuously corrugated, epomia inconspicuous; notaulus inconspicuously impressed, uniformly sculptured with mesoscutum, not reaching middle of mesoscutum; mesopleuron dorsal half medially faintly strigulate-rugulose, ventral half without distinct ridges or rugae, epicnemial carina restricted to ventral 0.7 of mesopleuron, posteriorly inconspicuously, densely corrugated; mesopleural groove markedly, sparsely corrugated; sternaulus entirely moderately corrugated; postpectal carina medially distinctly bent; metapleuron, subapical fovea shallow, subcircular; pleural carina stout; propodeum anterior area moderately long, PLL 1.03, anterior transverse carina distinct, complete, slightly, uniformly curved, posterior area strigulate-rugulose, with faint ridges medially moderately arched backwards (
<figureCitation box="[516,589,1008,1032]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[222,1364,155,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-118@56.[222,1364,155,1888]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Propodeum posterior area, dorsal, ♀. 7, Debilos soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 8, D. orthum sp. nov., Holotype. 9, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 10, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 11, D. palaior sp. nov., Holotype. 12, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 13, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 14, D. frater sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 7 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), spiracle distinctly elliptic, SWL 2.29, propodeal apophyses of regular height, thorn-shaped, AHD 2.06. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[591,676,1043,1067]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–72" captionStartId="62.[151,263,1290,1313]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1269]" captionTargetId="figure-182@62.[151,1435,193,1269]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 59–72. ♀. 59–70, hind tarsus, lateral. 59, D. orthum sp. nov., Holotype. 60, D. dnopheror sp. nov., Holotype. 61, D. petiolatum sp. nov., Holotype. 62, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 63, D. aserum sp. nov., Holotype. 64, D. anokum sp. nov., Holotype. 65, D. okarum sp. nov., Holotype. 66, D. makirum sp. nov., Holotype. 67, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 68, D. umentum sp. nov., Holotype. 69, D. masipum sp. nov., Holotype. 70, D. sanimum sp. nov., Holotype. 71, 72, hind t4, ventral, Holotypes. 71, D. dnopheror sp. nov. 72, D. dialeucor sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
): Hind t4 posterior lobe about 0.31 × as long as anterior lobe. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-153@58.[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. ♀. 25, Debilos palaior sp. nov., fore wing, dorsal. Specimen from Ecuador, Morona-Santiago, Cordillera de Cutucú, 28.III.1981 (BMNH). 26–28, fore and hind wings, dorsal, Holotypes. 26, D. soror (Trentepohl). 27, D. orthum sp. nov. 28, D. frater sp. nov., arrow: ramellus. 29, hind wing, dorsal, D. curtuvenatum sp. nov., Holotype. 30–33, fore and hind wings, dorsal. 30, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 31, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 32, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 33, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 26 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
): Fore wing vein (Rs+M)b perfectly straight, limit with crossvein 1m-cu distinct, ramellus absent; vein Rs&amp;1M uniformly slightly curved; crossvein 1cu-a straight, arising distinctly apicad vein Rs&amp;1M, by about 0.1– 0.2 × 1cu-a length, angle with vein M+Cu about 90 degrees; vein 2Cua moderately shorter than crossvein 2cu-a, FWC 0.67; areolet small, APH 0.71; vein 2Ma shorter to longer than vein 2Mb; vein 2Mb tubular; crossvein 2m-cu with bulla short, about 0.2 × as long as vein length or shorter; vein 2Rsb slightly sinuous, almost straight. Hind wing vein 2-1A long, reaching about 0.8 × the distance to wing margin, HWC 1.94.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[199,316,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[332,417,1292,1316]" captionStart="FIGURES 96–100" captionStartId="65.[151,263,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[198,1388,193,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-70@65.[198,1388,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 96–100. Holotypes, ♀, lateral. 96, Debilos orthum sp. nov. 97, D. gnampthum sp. nov. 98, D. frater sp. nov. 99, D. prionilix sp. nov. 100, D. crusilix sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). T1 petiole basal half smooth towards base, apical half, postpetiole coriarious-punctulate, except pospetiole apical parts centrally smooth, sparsely punctulate, spiracle at about basal 0.6, prominent, T1LW 3.07, T1WW 2.64, T1GL 0.29; T2 moderately short, apically robust, T2T1L 0.68, thyridium distinctly wider than long, T2LW 0.84, T2WW 2.20. Ovipositor approximately straight, OST 0.55, dorsal valve with nodus absent, notch absent; ventral valve tip without distinct serrations (
<figureCitation box="[801,885,1433,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="57.[151,263,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[253,1339,155,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-149@57.[252,1340,155,1849]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. ♀. 15, 16, T1, dorsal, Holotypes. 15, Debilos makirum sp. nov. 16, D. okarum sp. nov. 17, 18, thyridium, T2, lateral, Holotypes. 17, D. umentum sp. nov. 18, D. typurum sp. nov. 19–24, ovipositor tip, lateral. 19, D. soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 20, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype (se: serrations). 21, D. orthum sp. nov., Holotype. 22, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 23, D. indistinctum, Holotype. 24, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 19 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[199,263,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Color</emphasis>
. Head black, mesosoma, legs and metasoma black. Head: Scape apex ventrally lightest; flagellomeres 5– 10 dorsally white; mouth parts whitish (218, 216, 195), except mandible mostly and apex blackish. 
<taxonomicName authority=": Collar" authorityName="Collar" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma: Collar</taxonomicName>
medially, rather with sublateral mark, propleuron dorsal margin and ventro-lateral corner, and mesepimeron dorsal 0.2 whitish to white; transverse carinae anteriorly and posteriorly to axillary trough of metanotum lightest; propodeal apophyses white. Legs: Fore coxa, mid coxa apical half, hind coxa apical margin, fore and mid trochanters, hind trochanter basal margin, hind tibia basal 0.2 and hind t1 apical half, t2–4 entirely white (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,1646,1670]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–72" captionStartId="62.[151,263,1290,1313]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1269]" captionTargetId="figure-182@62.[151,1435,193,1269]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 59–72. ♀. 59–70, hind tarsus, lateral. 59, D. orthum sp. nov., Holotype. 60, D. dnopheror sp. nov., Holotype. 61, D. petiolatum sp. nov., Holotype. 62, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 63, D. aserum sp. nov., Holotype. 64, D. anokum sp. nov., Holotype. 65, D. okarum sp. nov., Holotype. 66, D. makirum sp. nov., Holotype. 67, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 68, D. umentum sp. nov., Holotype. 69, D. masipum sp. nov., Holotype. 70, D. sanimum sp. nov., Holotype. 71, 72, hind t4, ventral, Holotypes. 71, D. dnopheror sp. nov. 72, D. dialeucor sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), except dorsal black mark taking fore coxa basal 0.5, fore trochanter dorsal portion centrally and mid trochanter dorsally almost entirely blackish; hind trochanter apical margin dorsally whitish; femora basal 0.1 slightly lightest; fore femur ventrally whitish towards apex; fore and mid tibiae anteriorly and posteriorly, and tarsi, rather fore t1 and fore and mid t2–4, pale yellow (241, 224, 144) to whitish; tarsomeres 5 brownish (091, 065, 051). Wings: Hyaline. Metasoma: Slightly lightest towards apex; T1–5 apical margin distinctly lightest; T6–8 apical margin dorsally white; sternites medially white; ovipositor sheath dark brown (092, 054, 024), except basal 0.75 ventrally whitish; ovipositor brown (159, 113, 062).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" box="[199,392,1930,1954]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1930,1954]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,582,2025]" lastBlockId="32.[151,1436,151,823]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[199,332,1965,1990]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1965,1990]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Variability</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[343,447,1966,1990]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Holotype</typeStatus>
with median portion of postpectal carina short and very faint. 
<emphasis box="[1186,1251,1966,1990]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Color</emphasis>
: flagellomere 4 apical parts sometimes white; some specimens, including 
<typeStatus box="[810,911,2001,2025]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
, with collar entirely blackish, except medially slightly whitish; mesopleuron dorsally and scutellum apically sometimes with brownish tint; extension and brightness of lightest marks on legs variable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,823]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[199,335,222,247]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,222,247]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[525,643,223,247]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthum">
<emphasis box="[525,545,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[562,643,223,247]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">orthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (see item Species Delimitation), formed by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[1318,1436,223,247]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthum">
<emphasis box="[1318,1338,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1355,1436,223,247]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">orthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[199,366,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnampthum">
<emphasis box="[199,219,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[234,366,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">gnampthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[381,557,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthum">
<emphasis box="[381,557,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Debilos orthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[707,873,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnampthum">
<emphasis box="[707,727,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[741,873,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">gnampthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the pedicel and flagellomere 1 entirely black (
<emphasis box="[229,252,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">vs</emphasis>
. pedicel with a dorsal white mark and flagellomere 1 dorsally white), entirely propodeum anterior area moderately long, PLL 1.03 (
<emphasis box="[484,507,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">vs</emphasis>
. short, PLL 0.76), and anterior transverse carina slightly, uniformly curved (
<emphasis box="[1405,1428,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">vs</emphasis>
. medially distinctly arched forwards).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,823]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[199,333,403,427]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,403,427]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
From the Greek word 
<emphasis box="[592,667,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">orthon</emphasis>
, meaning “straight,” in reference to the anterior transverse carina of propodeum uniformly curved, almost straight at median portion in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
